com.soa.security.spi

Interface IdentityProfileProvider


  • public interface IdentityProfileProvider
    This is the SPI interface to create a Identity from a Identity profile.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      IdentityProfileSubjectMetaData createIdentityProfile(javax.security.auth.Subject profile, IProfileConfig config)
      Create a Identity Profile from the configuration, and the information related to this identity object should be stored in the Subject
      void destroyIdentityProfile(javax.security.auth.Subject profile)
      This metho is called when a specific profile is no longer needed.

    • Method Detail

      • createIdentityProfile

        IdentityProfileSubjectMetaData createIdentityProfile(javax.security.auth.Subject profile,
                                                     IProfileConfig config)
                                              throws InvalidConfigurationException
        Create a Identity Profile from the configuration, and the information related to this identity object should be stored in the Subject
        Parameters:
        profile - The Subject object that will hold the Principal and Credential related to this identity
        config - The configuration of this Identity Profile
        Throws:
        InvalidConfigurationException

      • destroyIdentityProfile

        void destroyIdentityProfile(javax.security.auth.Subject profile)
        This metho is called when a specific profile is no longer needed. Because the subject can contain principal/credential from multiple providers, it is important that the implementation of each provider should only release the resourcces it actually allocates.
        Parameters:
        profile -
